    {
      "id": "3f08cb83_8fa04e10",
      "file_path": "docs/openapi/openapi.yml",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 134,
      "message": "header -> accept looks like a field which should not be blank. It can be optional if we specify a default value as user don't need to provide it. \n\nAs we are returning response even if this parameter is missing there would be still some default content-type.\n\nBecause type is explicitly defined in the parameters, we should provide the default value too.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7680,
        "name": "Renu Kumari",
        "display_name": "Renu Kumari",
        "email": "kashi.renu@gmail.com",
        "username": "renukumari"
      },
      "updated": "2021-08-10 13:25:07.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "932bc0b5_1dcd75ef",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "728a93ba_00af618e",
      "file_path": "docs/openapi/openapi.yml",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 134,
      "message": "Accept parameter is indication to server from client that what kind of data format client accepts. Here if accept is nothing that means whatever format response data received from server then client will accept it. By giving default value IMO we will the override client's choice of accepting any kind of data format. \n\nAs data is not owned by dmi-plugin but by sdnc->node, so dmi-plugin should not act on behalf of client if nothing is coming.\n\nWhat do you think about it. Please comment.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5006,
        "name": "Rahul Tyagi",
        "display_name": "Rahul Tyagi",
        "email": "rahul.tyagi@est.tech",
        "username": "tragait"
      },
      "updated": "2021-08-10 13:37:15.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "3f08cb83_8fa04e10",
      "unresolved": true
    },
